<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1747,2013]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1747,1773]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[289,349,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male</emphasis>
: only species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaverri &amp; Borkent" authorityYear="2007" box="[561,654,1747,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dixidae</taxonomicName>
in Central America with a wide pale medial band on the pleura extending from the anterior margin of the katepisternum to the posterior margin of the anepimeron and with the gonostylus apically tapered (
<figureCitation box="[530,638,1827,1853]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,255,1996,2020]" captionTargetBox="[214,1361,502,1969]" captionTargetId="figure-142@21.[191,1411,451,2005]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Genitalia of male Dixella, dorsal view. (A) D. fernandezae; (B) D. jironi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096857" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096857/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[666,754,1828,1853]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Female</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1747,2013]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,152,1184]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,1867,1893]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[367,427,1868,1893]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[442,509,1867,1893]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[526,615,1867,1893]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[168,1416,300,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-91@4.[151,1436,277,1872]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Head capsules of male Dixella, anterior view. (A) D. maculata; (B) D. hernandezi; (C) D. shannoni; (D) D. hansoni; (E) D. fernandezae; (F) D. jironi; (G) D. venezuelensis; (H) D. woodi; (I) D. lobata; (J) D. suzukii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096835" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096835/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
): brown, densely spiculate, with spicules more elongate than those in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,298,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shannoni">
<emphasis box="[151,298,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">D. shannoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaverri and Borkent" authorityYear="2007" box="[318,452,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hansoni">
<emphasis box="[318,452,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">D. hansoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaverri and Borkent" authorityYear="2007" box="[471,654,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandezae">
<emphasis box="[471,654,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">D. fernandezae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Clypeus yellowish, as wide as long. Antennal scape, pedicel, flagellomeres yellowish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[457,550,1947,1973]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Thorax</emphasis>
: similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[688,834,1948,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shannoni">
<emphasis box="[688,834,1948,1973]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">D. shannoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[850,943,1947,1973]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[288,1337,265,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-84@6.[180,1424,178,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Thoraces of male Dixella, dorsal view. (A) D. maculata; (B) D. hernandezi; (C) D. shannoni; (D) D. hansoni." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096837/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[957,995,1947,1973]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,255,1473,1497]" captionTargetBox="[209,1349,191,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-232@8.[151,1436,90,1513]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thoraces of male Dixella, lateral view. (A) D. maculata; (B) D. hernandezi; (C) D. shannoni; (D) D. hansoni." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096841/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">4C</figureCitation>
). Scutum yellowish, with narrow lateral light brown band extending from anterior margin, widening near prescutal suture, continuing laterally to supraalar area, anterior to middle of scutum lateral band continues medially as faint yellow line, with row of setae to prescutellar area; acrostical, anterior dorsocentral, supraalar setae short, scattered. Scutellum, mediotergite brown. Pleura with 2 setae on posteroventral margin of posterior anepisternum. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1184,1252,231,257]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1269,1358,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,255,1607,1631]" captionTargetBox="[229,1364,197,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-139@12.[160,1427,128,1623]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Wings of male Dixella. (A) D. maculata; (B) D. hernandezi; (C) D. shannoni; (D) D. hansoni; (E) D. fernandezae; (F) D. jironi; (G) D. venezuelensis; (H) D. woodi; (I) D. lobata; (J) D. suzukii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096845" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096845/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,241,151,175]" captionText="TABLE 1. Length of wings of male Dixella in Costa Rica (in mm)" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Table 1</tableCitation>
): with or without slight darkening over r-m; R2+3 originating either at or slightly distal to r-m; stem of R2+3 0.40 length of R3. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[364,455,314,340]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Halter:</emphasis>
pale, 0.40 length of fore femur. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[842,900,314,340]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Legs</emphasis>
: yellowish; claws as figured (
<figureCitation box="[1253,1344,314,340]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1938,1962]" captionTargetBox="[171,1409,677,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-194@15.[129,1459,616,1914]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 8. Claws of male Dixella. (A) D. fernandezae; (B) D. jironi; (C) D. venezuelensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096849/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[222,329,357,383]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,255,1996,2020]" captionTargetBox="[214,1361,502,1969]" captionTargetId="figure-142@21.[191,1411,451,2005]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Genitalia of male Dixella, dorsal view. (A) D. fernandezae; (B) D. jironi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096857" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096857/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
): tergite 9 with anterior, posterior margins curved, with setae more dense along posterior margin. Sternite 9 with posterior margin with moderately narrow excavation, with 3–4 posterolateral setae. Gonocoxite longer than wide; basal lobe quadrate; apical lobe cylindrical, tusk-like, slightly curved dorsally, tip rounded, 0.6 length of gonostylus, with elongate basal seta, midlength seta as long as half lobe length, two short subapical setae. Gonostylus slightly wider at base and apex, apex rounded, with short subapical seta. Parameres dark brown, narrow, sinuous, pointed, apices directed posteriorly. Aedeagus triangular. Tergite10 light brown, posterior margin slightly bilobed, with four short subapical setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,152,1184]" box="[198,605,637,663]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[198,468,638,663]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Female and immatures</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,152,1184]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,546,677,703]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaverri and Borkent" authorityYear="2007" box="[560,718,678,703]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jironi">
<emphasis box="[560,718,678,703]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Dixella jironi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1003,1053,677,703]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[1185,1313,677,703]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
at 
<quantity box="[1348,1436,677,703]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="m" value="1700.0">1700 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,270,717,743]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="30.[151,255,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[253,1359,225,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-53@30.[222,1378,194,1942]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 18. Distributions of Dixella species in Costa Rica: (A) D. maculata—O; D. hernandezi–-, D. shannoni— ; (B) D. hansoni—O, D. fernandezae—, D. jironi— ." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096868/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Adults were swept from low vegetation near a small stream at the beginning of rainy season (May) in a habitat corresponding to Premontane Moist Forest.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,152,1184]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,478,797,823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Taxonomic discussion.</emphasis>
The male adult of this species shares the medial pale band on the thoracic pleura of 
<taxonomicName box="[183,327,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shannoni">
<emphasis box="[183,204,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[219,327,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">shannoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaverri and Borkent" authorityYear="2007" box="[384,513,838,863]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hansoni">
<emphasis box="[384,513,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">D. hansoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The apical lobe of the gonocoxite of the male genitalia is similar in the three species but in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaverri and Borkent" authorityYear="2007" box="[320,421,878,903]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jironi">
<emphasis box="[320,421,878,903]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">D. jironi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is longer, relative to the gonostylus. Further differences are present in the shape of the parameres, gonostyli and the tenth sternites of these three species (see key, 
<figureCitation box="[1075,1226,917,943]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,255,1743,1767]" captionTargetBox="[209,1364,238,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-108@19.[157,1429,146,1763]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Genitalia of male Dixella, dorsal view. (A) D. shannoni; (B) D. hansoni." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096855" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096855/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 11A, B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1239,1291,917,943]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,255,1996,2020]" captionTargetBox="[214,1361,502,1969]" captionTargetId="figure-142@21.[191,1411,451,2005]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Genitalia of male Dixella, dorsal view. (A) D. fernandezae; (B) D. jironi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096857" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096857/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">12B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,152,1184]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,280,957,983]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Types.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation accessionNumber="LN 209100" collectingDate="1999-05-31" collectionCode="CNCI" collectorName="A. Borkent" country="Costa Rica" elevation="1700" location="Alto Tapezco" municipality="Escazu" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" specimenCount="2" stateProvince="San Jose" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus box="[291,403,957,983]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Holotype</typeStatus>
, male adult on microscope slide, labeled “ 
<typeStatus box="[932,1090,957,983]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Chaverri and Borkent" authorityName="Chaverri and Borkent" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" genus="Dixella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jironi">
<emphasis box="[1103,1266,958,983]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Dixella jironi</emphasis>
Chaverri and Borkent
